bug.summary: malloc(): smallbin double linked list corrupted
bug.description:
<denchmark-h:h2>How to reproduce the behaviour</denchmark-h>
I'm frequently getting segmentation faults or related errors (such as the one described in this issue) when processing a list of documents with spaCy. Unfortunately, the error seems to be "non-deterministic", i.e. the error occurs at different documents, and when I isolate the document where the error occured in one run and only process this document with spaCy, there is no error.
